We’re looking for a Solutions Architect with expertise in Microsoft Dynamics 365 Customer Engagement and web technologies like Drupal to join our CXM Practice at Agilisys to lead the design of integrated solutions for modern digital citizen services. As a Solution Architect you will ensure that our designs are best in class and you will help develop capabilities required for customers of the future. As an experienced Solution Architect, you will manage solutions for our clients and using your development expertise help deliver large and complex projects. 1.1.1 About Our Organisation Stemming from one of UK’s leading digital venture builder, Agilisys is home to people that love solving complex problems and making change happen by having a passion for technology and digital disruption. As an Employee Owned business, our people are our main asset, and everyone has a real say in the direction that the business is heading. In Customer Experience Management (CXM) practice, we work with our clients to design and deliver solutions that can involve creation of services and operating models, building business cases and the subsequent change programmes; undertaking whole system/service evaluations or delivering complex multi-partner implementations – no job is the same. We bring an insightful, questioning and highly informed perspective and our people are driven by the quest to keep delivering next-generation business and digital solutions to solve our public and private sector clients' challenges.
Our Ethos: Agilisys’ entrepreneurial roots mean that our people are our differentiator and as an agile business, you have influence and the opportunity to make a difference. In CXM practice, we blend business acumen, experience, design and technology expertise seamlessly, so our clients can be more confident about the future. Therefore, taking the trusted advisor role, we shape and steer the new, helping our clients making sense of it. 1.1.2 Role As an Agilisys CXM Solution Architect, you will be designing digital customer solutions for our clients. You will need to bring together your experience of Microsoft Dynamics 365 and other solutions of the Microsoft cloud product family to translate our clients' visions in to clear technical designs, which you will promote, communicate and lead implementing. 1.1.2.1 Main duties ∙ Be a champion for both technical and functional solutions across the Microsoft platform, driving the adoption of new features and technology. ∙ Lead the design and development of sector specific templates to enhance the out of the box. ∙ Gather and document business needs, identify gaps between business needs and standard application functionality, design and document solutions that fill the gaps. ∙ Provide detailed business requirements specifications for developers. ∙ Develop complex solutions taking the lead role in across the development phase and elements of pre-sales. ∙ Develop and maintain business process documentation and consider compliance in all business process analysis and redesign activities. ∙ Perform application configuration, testing and evaluation to ensure quality and consistency. ∙ Develop, document, and execute test plans to assess the integrity and accuracy of business processes, module functionality setups and modifications, enhancements, customisations, and patches. 1.1.2.2 Experience ∙ Minimum of 5 years development experience using Microsoft technologies. ∙ Minimum of 3 years development experience in web technologies including ASP.NET, C#, Web Forms and/or MVC strongly preferred. ∙ Experience in pre-sales demonstrations, presentations, proposal writing, analysis/requirements gathering, producing Technical Design Documents. ∙ Lead engagement experience and presentation to the C-Suite stakeholders. ∙ Strong experience with .NET using C#. ∙ Experience in design patterns and unit/integration testing. ∙ Experience in implementing SOA and Microservice Architectures. ∙ Experience within a consulting environment. ∙ Experience of Microsoft Dynamics 365 through multiple project involvement with activities as follows:
∙ Installation and configuration of Microsoft Dynamics 365 ∙ UI customisation (both supported and unsupported) ∙ Custom application and web service development ∙ Ability to create SSRS reports (Fetch XML) ∙ SDK Usage
∙ Integration experience using custom applications and off-the-shelf products such as Biztalk or Scribe. 1.1.2.3 Skills ∙ Minimum 2:1 undergraduate degree with preference in either Business or Computer Science studies and Masters or MBA preferred. ∙ Minimum of MB2 - 716 Microsoft Dynamics 365 Customization and Configuration certified. ∙ Strong verbal and written communication skills, with an ability to articulate key messages clearly and explain technical concepts to a non-technical audience. ∙ Comfortable presenting to audiences including resources from all levels of organisation: business, IT, C-level. ∙ Have an exceptional understanding of Microsoft Dynamics 365 technical and functional capabilities.
